tracks.text: People in various locations put on headphones. A band member presses a button on a walkman.
A spiky haired latino man nods
An older black man in a park. Robert L. Clark, Venice Beach, California.
A black teenager in a parking lot. Jasmine James, High School Student.
A man with an afro nods. Jasmine removes her headphones and shakes her head.
Elizabeth Cullen, Accountant. A blond woman in glasses.
Q. T. Kenan, Technology Consultant.
Deidre Fitzpatrick, News Reporter. Bud Sparks, Souvenir Salesman.
Sandi Niklas, Dry Carpet Cleaner to the Stars
The news reporter laughs
Arthur Porter, Audio Visual Technician, stifles a laugh
Robbyn Seat, Junior High School Student, looks confused and blinks rapidly
Jim Soper, Retired Architect, frowns
Robert keeps jamming. The retired architect frowns more.
A man with an afro, Eric Quach, Web Designer, nods along by a tennis court.
Tammy Lu, College Student sits on a beach and furrows her brow
Steve Boeckels, Drug Sales Rep, wears a suit and loud tie on a street corner and bounces with the music.
A large, bearded man covered in tattoos. Kurt Skelton, Head Chef. He nods along while stopping his dog from chewing the headphone cord.
An older bearded man. Ralph Walbridge, Poet, takes off his headphone. Bruce Thiessen, Ph.D., Psychologist, sits on the street with a guitar.
Ren Wang Loi, Navigator, smiles nervously
Brooke Wilson, Flight Attendant / Nurse
Aaron Sugg, Cartoonist, a college aged white man wearing a black leather jacket
B N Duncan, Street Vendor
Robert Carpenter, Unemployed, A shirtless young man on a beach.
A young black woman pumps her fist and dances
Johnnie Mae, San Francisco, California, smiles and nods along
The sales rep dances widely in the street, while the cord to the walkman sways around
The junior high school student furrows her brow
The spiky haired latino, Maxx Garcia, Loan Purchaser, presses the headphones to his ears and smiles
The shirtless man smiles vacantly at the sky while holding up his fists and swaying
Tammy Thompson, Model/Songwriter, dances harder
Suzanne Panos, Home school student, a young girl with braces
The dry cleaner holds the headphones and dances.
A shirtless bearded man in tattoos wearing sunglasses at night, Rafe DeWitt, Unemployed.
The drug rep strikes a pose, takes off the headphones, and walks away with bags.
Jens Wallat, German Tourist. A tanned man with silver glasses, takes off his headphones.
Gina Zaritsky, Senior Art Director, Advertising. Cut to black.
